    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>Inflating the economy of a small remote island with only 250 people could have various consequences, depending on the specific circumstances and factors involved. Here are a few potential outcomes to consider:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Price inflation: If a significant amount of money is suddenly injected into the island's economy, there may not be enough goods and services available to meet the increased demand. This can cause prices to rise, leading to inflation. Local residents might find it difficult to afford essential items.</p>
</li>
