<p>Income disparities: If certain individuals or businesses on the island gain a sudden influx of wealth, it can create income disparities within the community. This can lead to social tensions and unequal distribution of resources.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Depreciation of local currency: If the island has its own currency, a sudden injection of funds could cause the value of the currency to depreciate. This can affect trade and further complicate economic stability.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Dependency on external support: If the island becomes heavily reliant on external support, such as continuous financial assistance or goods, it may lose its self-sustainability. This can lead to long-term economic challenges and difficulties once external support is withdrawn.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>It is crucial to consider the specific economic conditions and needs of the island, as well as engage in careful planning and consultation with local stakeholders, to ensure that any initiatives to support its growth are sustainable and do not cause unintended negative side effects.</p></div>

Simulate a person using an LLM. Respond like a regular person. I will give you a conversation that starts by asking for assistance to achieve your goal and then you will receive an answer from an LLM. If you goal achieved, you should not respond. If not, you will write the person's next response based on both previous turns! Generate only the last human response.<br/><br/>You said this to an LLM: <br/><div style="
    background-color: #e6f7ff;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
